<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1437,927,1997]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,998,1024]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Gustafsson &amp; Bush, 2022" authorityName="Gustafsson &amp; Bush" authorityYear="2022" box="[329,790,999,1025]" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Indoceoplanetes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Psocodea" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subarcens" status="new species" subGenus="Capnodella">
<emphasis box="[329,513,999,1025]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Indoceoplanetes</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[530,661,999,1025]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Capnodella</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[677,790,999,1025]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">subarcens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[798,935,998,1025]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[798,935,998,1025]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is most similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Gustafsson &amp; Bush, 2022" authorityName="Gustafsson &amp; Bush" authorityYear="2022" box="[1147,1324,999,1025]" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Indoceoplanetes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Psocodea" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="saucia" status="new species" subGenus="Capnodella">
<emphasis box="[1147,1178,999,1024]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">In.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1195,1234,999,1025]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Cp.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1251,1324,999,1024]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">saucia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="28" pageNumber="29" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, both sharing the following characters: preantennal head gently rounded (
<emphasis box="[1040,1068,1035,1061]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">cf.</emphasis>
<figureCitation box="[1076,1208,1035,1061]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 71–72" captionStart-1="FIGURES 73–82. 73" captionStartId-0="33.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionStartId-1="34.[151,264,1783,1807]" captionTargetBox-0="[194,1376,200,1910]" captionTargetBox-1="[254,1333,193,1750]" captionTargetId-0="figure-17@33.[190,1397,181,1920]" captionTargetId-1="figure-23@34.[236,1352,181,1759]" captionTargetPageId-0="33" captionTargetPageId-1="34" captionText-0="FIGURES 71–72. Male heads, dorsal and ventral views. 71, Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) kamphaengphetensis n. sp. ex Lalage melaschistos avensis. 72, Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) subarcens n. sp. ex Edolisoma melas melas." captionText-1="FIGURES 73–82. 73, Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) saucia n. sp. ex Edolisoma montanum montanum, male head, dorsal and ventral views. 74–82. Male Genitalia. Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) kamphaengphetensis n. sp. ex Lalage melaschistos avensis: 74, dorsal view. 75, male mesosome, ventral view. 76, male paramere, dorsal view. Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) subarcens n. sp. ex Edolisoma melas melas: 77, dorsal view. 78, male mesosome, ventral view. 79, male paramere, dorsal view. Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) saucia n. sp. ex Edolisoma montanum montanum: 80, dorsal view. 81, male mesosome, ventral view. 82, male paramere, dorsal view. Abbreviations: ames = anterior mesosomal seta; gpmes = gonoporal posterior mesosomal seta; lpmes = lateral posterior mesosomal seta; pst1–2 = parameral setae 1–2." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825595" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825597" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/6825595/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/6825597/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Figs 72–73</figureCitation>
); dorsal preantennal suture extends median to 
<emphasis box="[437,476,1071,1097]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">ads</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[492,520,1071,1097]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">cf.</emphasis>
<figureCitation box="[526,656,1071,1097]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 71–72" captionStart-1="FIGURES 73–82. 73" captionStartId-0="33.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionStartId-1="34.[151,264,1783,1807]" captionTargetBox-0="[194,1376,200,1910]" captionTargetBox-1="[254,1333,193,1750]" captionTargetId-0="figure-17@33.[190,1397,181,1920]" captionTargetId-1="figure-23@34.[236,1352,181,1759]" captionTargetPageId-0="33" captionTargetPageId-1="34" captionText-0="FIGURES 71–72. Male heads, dorsal and ventral views. 71, Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) kamphaengphetensis n. sp. ex Lalage melaschistos avensis. 72, Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) subarcens n. sp. ex Edolisoma melas melas." captionText-1="FIGURES 73–82. 73, Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) saucia n. sp. ex Edolisoma montanum montanum, male head, dorsal and ventral views. 74–82. Male Genitalia. Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) kamphaengphetensis n. sp. ex Lalage melaschistos avensis: 74, dorsal view. 75, male mesosome, ventral view. 76, male paramere, dorsal view. Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) subarcens n. sp. ex Edolisoma melas melas: 77, dorsal view. 78, male mesosome, ventral view. 79, male paramere, dorsal view. Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) saucia n. sp. ex Edolisoma montanum montanum: 80, dorsal view. 81, male mesosome, ventral view. 82, male paramere, dorsal view. Abbreviations: ames = anterior mesosomal seta; gpmes = gonoporal posterior mesosomal seta; lpmes = lateral posterior mesosomal seta; pst1–2 = parameral setae 1–2." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825595" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825597" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/6825595/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/6825597/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Figs 72–73</figureCitation>
); abdominal segment IV in both sexes with 2 
<emphasis box="[1168,1193,1071,1096]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">ps</emphasis>
on each side (
<emphasis box="[1354,1382,1071,1097]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">cf.</emphasis>
<figureCitation captionStart-0="FIGURES 64–65" captionStart-1="FIGURES 66–67" captionStartId-0="29.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionStartId-1="31.[151,264,1927,1951]" captionTargetBox-0="[238,1352,196,1916]" captionTargetBox-1="[227,1387,201,1892]" captionTargetId-0="figure-17@29.[222,1366,181,1919]" captionTargetId-1="figure-17@31.[151,1436,181,1904]" captionTargetPageId-0="29" captionTargetPageId-1="31" captionText-0="FIGURES 64–65. Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) subarcens n. sp. ex Edolisoma melas melas: 64, male habitus, dorsal and ventral views. 65, female habitus, dorsal and ventral views." captionText-1="FIGURES 66–67. Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) saucia n. sp. ex Edolisoma montanum montanum. 66, male habitus, dorsal and ventral views. 67, female habitus, dorsal and ventral views." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825589" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825591" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/6825589/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/6825591/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Figs 64–67</figureCitation>
); vulval margin gently rounded (
<emphasis box="[593,621,1107,1133]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">cf.</emphasis>
<figureCitation box="[627,757,1107,1133]" captionStart="FIGURES 68–70. 68" captionStartId="32.[151,264,1854,1878]" captionTargetBox="[151,1429,195,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-23@32.[151,1436,181,1831]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURES 68–70. 68, Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) kamphaengphetensis n. sp. ex Lalage melaschistos avensis, male habitus, dorsal and ventral views. 69, Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) subarcens n. sp. ex Edolisoma melas melas, female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view. 70, Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) saucia n. sp. ex Edolisoma montanum montanum, female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825593" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825593/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Figs 69–70</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1437,927,1997]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
These two species can be separated by the following characters: female abdominal segments V–VI with 2 
<emphasis box="[1377,1402,1143,1168]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">ps</emphasis>
on each side in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gustafsson &amp; Bush" authorityYear="2022" box="[292,469,1179,1205]" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Indoceoplanetes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Psocodea" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="saucia" subGenus="Capnodella">
<emphasis box="[292,323,1179,1204]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">In.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[339,379,1179,1205]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Cp.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[396,469,1179,1204]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">saucia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[485,569,1179,1205]" captionStart="FIGURES 66–67" captionStartId="31.[151,264,1927,1951]" captionTargetBox="[227,1387,201,1892]" captionTargetId="figure-17@31.[151,1436,181,1904]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURES 66–67. Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) saucia n. sp. ex Edolisoma montanum montanum. 66, male habitus, dorsal and ventral views. 67, female habitus, dorsal and ventral views." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825591" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825591/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 67</figureCitation>
), but with 3 
<emphasis box="[712,737,1179,1204]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">ps</emphasis>
on each side in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gustafsson &amp; Bush" authorityYear="2022" box="[921,1138,1179,1205]" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Indoceoplanetes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Psocodea" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subarcens" subGenus="Capnodella">
<emphasis box="[921,952,1179,1204]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">In.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[968,1008,1179,1205]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Cp.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1025,1138,1179,1205]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">subarcens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1153,1237,1178,1205]" captionStart="FIGURES 64–65" captionStartId="29.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[238,1352,196,1916]" captionTargetId="figure-17@29.[222,1366,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURES 64–65. Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) subarcens n. sp. ex Edolisoma melas melas: 64, male habitus, dorsal and ventral views. 65, female habitus, dorsal and ventral views." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825589" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825589/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 65</figureCitation>
); proximal mesosome broadly flattened in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gustafsson &amp; Bush" authorityYear="2022" box="[438,651,1215,1241]" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Indoceoplanetes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Psocodea" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subarcens" subGenus="Capnodella">
<emphasis box="[438,469,1215,1240]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">In.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[484,523,1215,1241]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Cp.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[538,651,1215,1241]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">subarcens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[665,747,1215,1241]" captionStart="FIGURES 73–82. 73" captionStartId="34.[151,264,1783,1807]" captionTargetBox="[254,1333,193,1750]" captionTargetId="figure-23@34.[236,1352,181,1759]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURES 73–82. 73, Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) saucia n. sp. ex Edolisoma montanum montanum, male head, dorsal and ventral views. 74–82. Male Genitalia. Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) kamphaengphetensis n. sp. ex Lalage melaschistos avensis: 74, dorsal view. 75, male mesosome, ventral view. 76, male paramere, dorsal view. Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) subarcens n. sp. ex Edolisoma melas melas: 77, dorsal view. 78, male mesosome, ventral view. 79, male paramere, dorsal view. Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) saucia n. sp. ex Edolisoma montanum montanum: 80, dorsal view. 81, male mesosome, ventral view. 82, male paramere, dorsal view. Abbreviations: ames = anterior mesosomal seta; gpmes = gonoporal posterior mesosomal seta; lpmes = lateral posterior mesosomal seta; pst1–2 = parameral setae 1–2." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825597" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825597/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 78</figureCitation>
), but rounded in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gustafsson &amp; Bush" authorityYear="2022" box="[932,1105,1215,1241]" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Indoceoplanetes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Psocodea" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="saucia" subGenus="Capnodella">
<emphasis box="[932,963,1215,1240]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">In.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[978,1017,1215,1241]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Cp.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1032,1105,1215,1240]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">saucia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1119,1201,1215,1241]" captionStart="FIGURES 73–82. 73" captionStartId="34.[151,264,1783,1807]" captionTargetBox="[254,1333,193,1750]" captionTargetId="figure-23@34.[236,1352,181,1759]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURES 73–82. 73, Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) saucia n. sp. ex Edolisoma montanum montanum, male head, dorsal and ventral views. 74–82. Male Genitalia. Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) kamphaengphetensis n. sp. ex Lalage melaschistos avensis: 74, dorsal view. 75, male mesosome, ventral view. 76, male paramere, dorsal view. Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) subarcens n. sp. ex Edolisoma melas melas: 77, dorsal view. 78, male mesosome, ventral view. 79, male paramere, dorsal view. Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) saucia n. sp. ex Edolisoma montanum montanum: 80, dorsal view. 81, male mesosome, ventral view. 82, male paramere, dorsal view. Abbreviations: ames = anterior mesosomal seta; gpmes = gonoporal posterior mesosomal seta; lpmes = lateral posterior mesosomal seta; pst1–2 = parameral setae 1–2." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825597" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825597/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 81</figureCitation>
); shape of gonopores (
<emphasis box="[161,189,1251,1277]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">cf.</emphasis>
<figureCitation box="[195,323,1251,1277]" captionStart="FIGURES 73–82. 73" captionStartId="34.[151,264,1783,1807]" captionTargetBox="[254,1333,193,1750]" captionTargetId="figure-23@34.[236,1352,181,1759]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURES 73–82. 73, Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) saucia n. sp. ex Edolisoma montanum montanum, male head, dorsal and ventral views. 74–82. Male Genitalia. Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) kamphaengphetensis n. sp. ex Lalage melaschistos avensis: 74, dorsal view. 75, male mesosome, ventral view. 76, male paramere, dorsal view. Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) subarcens n. sp. ex Edolisoma melas melas: 77, dorsal view. 78, male mesosome, ventral view. 79, male paramere, dorsal view. Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) saucia n. sp. ex Edolisoma montanum montanum: 80, dorsal view. 81, male mesosome, ventral view. 82, male paramere, dorsal view. Abbreviations: ames = anterior mesosomal seta; gpmes = gonoporal posterior mesosomal seta; lpmes = lateral posterior mesosomal seta; pst1–2 = parameral setae 1–2." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825597" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825597/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Figs 78, 81</figureCitation>
); female subgenital plate broader and more rounded distally in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gustafsson &amp; Bush" authorityYear="2022" box="[1033,1209,1251,1277]" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Indoceoplanetes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Psocodea" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="saucia" subGenus="Capnodella">
<emphasis box="[1033,1064,1251,1276]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">In.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1080,1120,1251,1277]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Cp.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1136,1209,1251,1276]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">saucia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1225,1306,1251,1277]" captionStart="FIGURES 68–70. 68" captionStartId="32.[151,264,1854,1878]" captionTargetBox="[151,1429,195,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-23@32.[151,1436,181,1831]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURES 68–70. 68, Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) kamphaengphetensis n. sp. ex Lalage melaschistos avensis, male habitus, dorsal and ventral views. 69, Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) subarcens n. sp. ex Edolisoma melas melas, female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view. 70, Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) saucia n. sp. ex Edolisoma montanum montanum, female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825593" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825593/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 70</figureCitation>
) than in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gustafsson &amp; Bush" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Indoceoplanetes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Psocodea" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subarcens" subGenus="Capnodella">
<emphasis box="[1406,1437,1251,1276]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">In.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[161,200,1287,1313]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Cp.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[217,330,1287,1313]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">subarcens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[344,429,1287,1313]" captionStart="FIGURES 68–70. 68" captionStartId="32.[151,264,1854,1878]" captionTargetBox="[151,1429,195,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-23@32.[151,1436,181,1831]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURES 68–70. 68, Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) kamphaengphetensis n. sp. ex Lalage melaschistos avensis, male habitus, dorsal and ventral views. 69, Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) subarcens n. sp. ex Edolisoma melas melas, female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view. 70, Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) saucia n. sp. ex Edolisoma montanum montanum, female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825593" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825593/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 69</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1437,927,1997]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,484,1322,1349]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
Description. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[353,478,1322,1349]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Both sexes</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Head flat dome-shaped (
<figureCitation box="[770,855,1323,1349]" captionStart="FIGURES 71–72" captionStartId="33.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[194,1376,200,1910]" captionTargetId="figure-17@33.[190,1397,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURES 71–72. Male heads, dorsal and ventral views. 71, Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) kamphaengphetensis n. sp. ex Lalage melaschistos avensis. 72, Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) subarcens n. sp. ex Edolisoma melas melas." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825595" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825595/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 72</figureCitation>
), lateral margins of preantennal head convex, frons rounded. Marginal carina broad, narrowing conspicuously near 
<emphasis box="[867,923,1359,1385]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">dsms</emphasis>
, interrupted submedianly. Dorsal preantennal suture reaching 
<emphasis box="[328,384,1395,1421]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">dsms</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[437,476,1395,1421]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">ads</emphasis>
, continuing median to 
<emphasis box="[731,770,1395,1421]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">ads</emphasis>
, but not completely separating dorsal anterior plate, and not reaching lateral head margins. Dorsal anterior plate broader than long, lateral margins irregular; sinuous thickening in posterior part. Ventral anterior plate diffuse, rounded rectangular. Head chaetotaxy as in 
<figureCitation box="[1211,1293,1467,1493]" captionStart="FIGURES 71–72" captionStartId="33.[151,264,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[194,1376,200,1910]" captionTargetId="figure-17@33.[190,1397,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURES 71–72. Male heads, dorsal and ventral views. 71, Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) kamphaengphetensis n. sp. ex Lalage melaschistos avensis. 72, Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) subarcens n. sp. ex Edolisoma melas melas." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825595" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825595/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 72</figureCitation>
. Preantennal nodi large, elongated, bulging. Pre- and postocular nodi of roughly equal size. Marginal temporal carina slender, of roughly even width. Gular plate with slightly concave lateral margins converging on median point. Thoracic and abdominal segments as in 
<figureCitation box="[447,575,1574,1601]" captionStart="FIGURES 64–65" captionStartId="29.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[238,1352,196,1916]" captionTargetId="figure-17@29.[222,1366,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURES 64–65. Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) subarcens n. sp. ex Edolisoma melas melas: 64, male habitus, dorsal and ventral views. 65, female habitus, dorsal and ventral views." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825589" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825589/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Figs 64–65</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1437,927,1997]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,265,1610,1637]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Male.</emphasis>
Thoracic and abdominal chaetotaxy as in 
<figureCitation box="[752,836,1611,1637]" captionStart="FIGURES 64–65" captionStartId="29.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[238,1352,196,1916]" captionTargetId="figure-17@29.[222,1366,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURES 64–65. Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) subarcens n. sp. ex Edolisoma melas melas: 64, male habitus, dorsal and ventral views. 65, female habitus, dorsal and ventral views." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825589" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825589/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 64</figureCitation>
; segment IV with 2 
<emphasis box="[1072,1097,1611,1636]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">ps</emphasis>
on each side. Basal apodeme roughly rectangular, but expanding markedly in distal section (
<figureCitation box="[850,934,1647,1673]" captionStart="FIGURES 73–82. 73" captionStartId="34.[151,264,1783,1807]" captionTargetBox="[254,1333,193,1750]" captionTargetId="figure-23@34.[236,1352,181,1759]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURES 73–82. 73, Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) saucia n. sp. ex Edolisoma montanum montanum, male head, dorsal and ventral views. 74–82. Male Genitalia. Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) kamphaengphetensis n. sp. ex Lalage melaschistos avensis: 74, dorsal view. 75, male mesosome, ventral view. 76, male paramere, dorsal view. Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) subarcens n. sp. ex Edolisoma melas melas: 77, dorsal view. 78, male mesosome, ventral view. 79, male paramere, dorsal view. Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) saucia n. sp. ex Edolisoma montanum montanum: 80, dorsal view. 81, male mesosome, ventral view. 82, male paramere, dorsal view. Abbreviations: ames = anterior mesosomal seta; gpmes = gonoporal posterior mesosomal seta; lpmes = lateral posterior mesosomal seta; pst1–2 = parameral setae 1–2." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825597" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825597/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 77</figureCitation>
). Proximal mesosome broadly flattened (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 73–82. 73" captionStartId="34.[151,264,1783,1807]" captionTargetBox="[254,1333,193,1750]" captionTargetId="figure-23@34.[236,1352,181,1759]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURES 73–82. 73, Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) saucia n. sp. ex Edolisoma montanum montanum, male head, dorsal and ventral views. 74–82. Male Genitalia. Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) kamphaengphetensis n. sp. ex Lalage melaschistos avensis: 74, dorsal view. 75, male mesosome, ventral view. 76, male paramere, dorsal view. Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) subarcens n. sp. ex Edolisoma melas melas: 77, dorsal view. 78, male mesosome, ventral view. 79, male paramere, dorsal view. Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) saucia n. sp. ex Edolisoma montanum montanum: 80, dorsal view. 81, male mesosome, ventral view. 82, male paramere, dorsal view. Abbreviations: ames = anterior mesosomal seta; gpmes = gonoporal posterior mesosomal seta; lpmes = lateral posterior mesosomal seta; pst1–2 = parameral setae 1–2." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825597" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825597/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 78</figureCitation>
). Mesosomal lobes only partially overlapping parameral heads. Gonopore as in 
<figureCitation box="[1104,1189,1683,1709]" captionStart="FIGURES 73–82. 73" captionStartId="34.[151,264,1783,1807]" captionTargetBox="[254,1333,193,1750]" captionTargetId="figure-23@34.[236,1352,181,1759]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURES 73–82. 73, Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) saucia n. sp. ex Edolisoma montanum montanum, male head, dorsal and ventral views. 74–82. Male Genitalia. Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) kamphaengphetensis n. sp. ex Lalage melaschistos avensis: 74, dorsal view. 75, male mesosome, ventral view. 76, male paramere, dorsal view. Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) subarcens n. sp. ex Edolisoma melas melas: 77, dorsal view. 78, male mesosome, ventral view. 79, male paramere, dorsal view. Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) saucia n. sp. ex Edolisoma montanum montanum: 80, dorsal view. 81, male mesosome, ventral view. 82, male paramere, dorsal view. Abbreviations: ames = anterior mesosomal seta; gpmes = gonoporal posterior mesosomal seta; lpmes = lateral posterior mesosomal seta; pst1–2 = parameral setae 1–2." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825597" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825597/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 78</figureCitation>
; distal margin deeply incised medianly, antero-lateral extensions slightly curved. Parameres broad throughout; 
<emphasis box="[1145,1219,1719,1745]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">pst1–2</emphasis>
as in 
<figureCitation box="[1285,1367,1719,1745]" captionStart="FIGURES 73–82. 73" captionStartId="34.[151,264,1783,1807]" captionTargetBox="[254,1333,193,1750]" captionTargetId="figure-23@34.[236,1352,181,1759]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURES 73–82. 73, Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) saucia n. sp. ex Edolisoma montanum montanum, male head, dorsal and ventral views. 74–82. Male Genitalia. Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) kamphaengphetensis n. sp. ex Lalage melaschistos avensis: 74, dorsal view. 75, male mesosome, ventral view. 76, male paramere, dorsal view. Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) subarcens n. sp. ex Edolisoma melas melas: 77, dorsal view. 78, male mesosome, ventral view. 79, male paramere, dorsal view. Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) saucia n. sp. ex Edolisoma montanum montanum: 80, dorsal view. 81, male mesosome, ventral view. 82, male paramere, dorsal view. Abbreviations: ames = anterior mesosomal seta; gpmes = gonoporal posterior mesosomal seta; lpmes = lateral posterior mesosomal seta; pst1–2 = parameral setae 1–2." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825597" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825597/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 79</figureCitation>
. Measurements as in 
<tableCitation box="[330,414,1755,1781]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="47.[151,239,457,483]" captionText="TABLE 1. Measurements (in mm) of species treated in this paper. Abbreviations used: TL = total length; HL = head length (along midline); HW = head width (at temples); PRW = prothorax width; PTW = pterothorax width; AW = abdominal width (at segment V). Note: many specimens had distorted abdomens, as noted below; consequently, the TL of many specimens could not be measured. Mean values are given in parentheses only where 10 or more individuals were measured. N = number of specimens examined." pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Table 1</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1437,927,1997]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,293,1790,1817]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Female.</emphasis>
Thoracic and abdominal chaetotaxy as in 
<figureCitation box="[767,850,1790,1817]" captionStart="FIGURES 64–65" captionStartId="29.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[238,1352,196,1916]" captionTargetId="figure-17@29.[222,1366,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURES 64–65. Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) subarcens n. sp. ex Edolisoma melas melas: 64, male habitus, dorsal and ventral views. 65, female habitus, dorsal and ventral views." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825589" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825589/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 65</figureCitation>
; segment IV with 2 
<emphasis box="[1076,1101,1791,1816]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">ps</emphasis>
on each side; segments V–VI with 3 
<emphasis box="[227,252,1827,1852]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">ps</emphasis>
on each side. Subgenital plate pentagonal (
<figureCitation box="[733,817,1827,1853]" captionStart="FIGURES 68–70. 68" captionStartId="32.[151,264,1854,1878]" captionTargetBox="[151,1429,195,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-23@32.[151,1436,181,1831]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURES 68–70. 68, Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) kamphaengphetensis n. sp. ex Lalage melaschistos avensis, male habitus, dorsal and ventral views. 69, Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) subarcens n. sp. ex Edolisoma melas melas, female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view. 70, Indoceoplanetes (Capnodella) saucia n. sp. ex Edolisoma montanum montanum, female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825593" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825593/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 69</figureCitation>
). Vulval margin gently rounded, with 1–2 short, slender 
<emphasis box="[151,195,1863,1888]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">vms</emphasis>
and 3–5 short, thorn-like 
<emphasis box="[496,530,1863,1888]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">vss</emphasis>
on each side; 5–10 slender 
<emphasis box="[853,890,1863,1888]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">vos</emphasis>
on each side of subgenital plate; distal 2–4 
<emphasis box="[1399,1436,1863,1888]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">vos</emphasis>
positioned median to 
<emphasis box="[393,427,1899,1924]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">vss</emphasis>
, and markedly longer than 
<emphasis box="[735,779,1899,1924]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">vms</emphasis>
. Measurements as in 
<tableCitation box="[1022,1105,1899,1925]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="47.[151,239,457,483]" captionText="TABLE 1. Measurements (in mm) of species treated in this paper. Abbreviations used: TL = total length; HL = head length (along midline); HW = head width (at temples); PRW = prothorax width; PTW = pterothorax width; AW = abdominal width (at segment V). Note: many specimens had distorted abdomens, as noted below; consequently, the TL of many specimens could not be measured. Mean values are given in parentheses only where 10 or more individuals were measured. N = number of specimens examined." pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Table 1</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1437,927,1997]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1935,1961]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species epithet is derived from Latin “ 
<emphasis box="[822,861,1935,1961]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">sub</emphasis>
-” for “almost” and Latin “ 
<emphasis box="[1164,1238,1935,1960]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">arcens</emphasis>
” for “enclosing”, referring to the almost transversally complete dorsal preantennal suture.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825589" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6825589" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825589/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" startId="29.[151,264,1943,1967]" targetBox="[238,1352,196,1916]" targetPageId="29">
